            </table>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- ARCHITECTURE -->
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-100">
            <h2 id="architecture" style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">3. Architecture Overview</h2>

            <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">3.1 System Design (Key Change: Metadata-Only Index)</h3>
            <div style="background: rgba(255,255,255,0.15); padding: var(--spacing-medium); border-radius: 5px; margin: var(--spacing-medium) 0; font-family: var(--body-font); color: var(--text-color);">
                <p><strong>Important:</strong> .tt files remain on disk as the source of truth. The database stores ONLY metadata (file_path, title, content_hash, role_permissions). When search happens:</p>
                <ol>
                    <li>User query → Search metadata_index via FULLTEXT</li>
                    <li>Return top matches with file_path + excerpt from disk</li>
                    <li>If .tt file changes → hash changes → re-index on next access</li>
                    <li>PyCharm IDE AI assistants can read database (if supported) OR read .tt files directly</li>
                </ol>
            </div>

            <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">3.2 Widget Visibility by User Type</h3>
            <table style="width: 100%; color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); border-collapse: collapse; margin: var(--spacing-medium) 0;">
                <thead>
                    <tr style="background: var(--secondary-color, #0066cc); color: white;">
                        <th style="padding: var(--spacing-small); text-align: left; border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">User Type</th>
                        <th style="padding: var(--spacing-small); text-align: left; border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">Can Access Widget</th>
                        <th style="padding: var(--spacing-small); text-align: left; border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">Models Available</th>
                        <th style="padding: var(--spacing-small); text-align: left; border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">Can Search Code</th>
                        <th style="padding: var(--spacing-small); text-align: left; border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">Can Use Web Search</th>
                    </tr>
                </thead>
                <tbody>
                    <tr style="background: rgba(255,255,255,0.15);">
                        <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">Non-Authenticated</td>
                        <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">✅ Yes (limited docs)</td>
                        <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">Ollama only</td>
                        <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">❌ No</td>
                        <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">❌ No</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">Normal User</td>
                        <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">✅ Yes</td>
                        <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">Ollama only</td>
                        <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">❌ No</td>
                        <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">⚙️ Configurable</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr style="background: rgba(255,255,255,0.15);">
                        <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">Developer/Editor</td>
                        <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">✅ Yes</td>
                        <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">Ollama + XAI</td>
                        <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">✅ Yes</td>
                        <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">✅ Yes</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">Admin</td>
                        <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">✅ Yes</td>
                        <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">Ollama + XAI</td>
                        <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">✅ Yes</td>
                        <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">✅ Yes</td>
                    </tr>
                </tbody>
            </table>

            <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">3.3 Documentation Audit Status - Result Class Implementation Verification</h3>
            <div style="background: var(--warning-color, #fff3cd); border-left: 4px solid var(--warning-border, #ff9800); padding: var(--spacing-medium); margin: var(--spacing-medium) 0; border-radius: 3px;">
                <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); margin-top: 0;"><strong>🔍 Audit Focus:</strong> Verify that AI Chat System documentation correctly describes using DBIx::Class Result classes (not raw SQL files) for table creation and schema management.</p>
            </div>

            <h4 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">Related Documentation Files Status</h4>
            <table style="width: 100%; color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); border-collapse: collapse; margin: var(--spacing-medium) 0;">
                <thead>
                    <tr style="background: var(--secondary-color, #0066cc); color: white;">
                        <th style="padding: var(--spacing-small); text-align: left; border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">Documentation File</th>
                        <th style="padding: var(--spacing-small); text-align: left; border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">Version</th>
                        <th style="padding: var(--spacing-small); text-align: left; border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">Result Class Accuracy</th>
                        <th style="padding: var(--spacing-small); text-align: left; border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">Status</th>
                    </tr>
                </thead>
                <tbody>
                    <tr style="background: rgba(255,255,255,0.15);">
                        <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);"><strong><a href="/Documentation/AI_Chat_Schema_Documentation" target="_blank" style="color: var(--link-color);">AI_Chat_Schema_Documentation.tt</a></strong></td>
                        <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">0.01</td>
                        <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">✅ Excellent - Explicitly states "DBIx::Class Result classes (not raw SQL files)"</td>
                        <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">✅ CORRECT</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);"><strong><a href="/Documentation/DBSchemaManager_Usage_Guide" target="_blank" style="color: var(--link-color);">DBSchemaManager_Usage_Guide.tt</a></strong></td>
                        <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">1.0 ⚠️</td>
                        <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">🟠 Partial - Correct content but missing explicit Result class emphasis</td>
                        <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">⚠️ NEEDS CORRECTION</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr style="background: rgba(255,255,255,0.15);">
                        <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);"><strong><a href="/Documentation/Schema" target="_blank" style="color: var(--link-color);">Schema.tt</a></strong></td>
                        <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">0.1 (outdated)</td>
                        <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">❌ Critical - Describes SQL migration approach, no mention of Result classes</td>
                        <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">❌ INCORRECT</td>
                    </tr>
                </tbody>
            </table>

            <h4 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">Critical Findings</h4>
            <div style="background: rgba(255,255,255,0.15); padding: var(--spacing-medium); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); margin: var(--spacing-small) 0;">
                <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                    <li><strong>✅ Best Practice Found:</strong> <a href="/Documentation/AI_Chat_Schema_Documentation" target="_blank" style="color: var(--link-color);">AI_Chat_Schema_Documentation.tt</a> correctly emphasizes Result classes in Overview section (line 47): "This schema is built using <em>DBIx::Class Result classes</em> (not raw SQL files) for type safety and version control"</li>
                    <li><strong>⚠️ Version Issue:</strong> <a href="/Documentation/DBSchemaManager_Usage_Guide" target="_blank" style="color: var(--link-color);">DBSchemaManager_Usage_Guide.tt</a> uses page_version "1.0" instead of "0.01" per documentation standards</li>
                    <li><strong>❌ Critical Gap:</strong> <a href="/Documentation/Schema" target="_blank" style="color: var(--link-color);">Schema.tt</a> is completely outdated, references SQL migration scripts and .sql file imports instead of Result class pattern</li>
                    <li><strong>⚠️ Content Gap:</strong> <a href="/Documentation/DBSchemaManager_Usage_Guide" target="_blank" style="color: var(--link-color);">DBSchemaManager</a> guide needs explicit mention that it works with Result classes, not SQL files</li>
                    <li><strong>✅ Consistency:</strong> AI_CHAT_DOCUMENTATION_FEATURE_SPEC.tt (this file) correctly references Result classes in Database Schema section (4.1-4.3)</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <h4 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">Recommended Actions</h4>
            <div style="background: rgba(255,255,255,0.15); padding: var(--spacing-medium); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); margin: var(--spacing-small) 0;">
                <ol style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                    <li><strong>Priority 1:</strong> Fix <a href="/Documentation/DBSchemaManager_Usage_Guide" target="_blank" style="color: var(--link-color);">DBSchemaManager_Usage_Guide.tt</a> - Change page_version from "1.0" to "0.01" and add section on "Result Classes First" approach</li>
                    <li><strong>Priority 1:</strong> Rewrite <a href="/Documentation/Schema" target="_blank" style="color: var(--link-color);">Schema.tt</a> - Remove SQL migration approach, replace with Result class creation workflow using <a href="/Documentation/DBSchemaManager_Usage_Guide" target="_blank" style="color: var(--link-color);">DBSchemaManager</a></li>
                    <li><strong>Priority 2:</strong> Add cross-reference links between all three documentation files for consistency</li>
                    <li><strong>Priority 2:</strong> Create unified "Schema Management Best Practices" section referencing all three guides</li>
                </ol>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- DATABASE SCHEMA -->
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-100">
            <h2 id="database-schema" style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">4. Database Schema (Using Existing Tables + New Extensions)</h2>

            <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">4.1 Extend Existing: ai_messages Table</h3>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Location:</strong> <a href="/Documentation/Result_Class_Development_Guide" target="_blank" style="color: var(--link-color);">/lib/Comserv/Model/Schema/Ency/Result/AiMessage.pm</a> (EXTEND existing fields)</p>
            <div style="background: rgba(255,255,255,0.15); padding: var(--spacing-medium); border-radius: 5px; margin: var(--spacing-medium) 0; overflow-x: auto;">
                <pre style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: monospace; margin: 0; font-size: var(--font-size-small);"><code>Fields to ADD to existing AiMessage table:
  agent_type => 'enum' (documentation, helpdesk, ency, beekeeping, hamradio, etc.)
  model_used => 'varchar' (ollama, xai, web)
  search_context => 'json' (which docs/code were searched)
  sources_cited => 'json' ([{file, title, excerpt, type}])
  user_role => 'varchar' (track user role at time of query)
  response_time_ms => 'integer' (performance tracking)
  tokens_used => 'integer' (for XAI cost tracking)
  is_verified => 'boolean' (only for web search results)
</code></pre>
            </div>

            <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">4.2 New Table: documentation_metadata_index</h3>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Location:</strong> <a href="/Documentation/Result_Class_Development_Guide" target="_blank" style="color: var(--link-color);">/lib/Comserv/Model/Schema/Ency/Result/DocumentationMetadataIndex.pm</a></p>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Purpose:</strong> Stores ONLY metadata and searchable excerpts of .tt files. Full content remains on disk.</p>
            <div style="background: rgba(255,255,255,0.15); padding: var(--spacing-medium); border-radius: 5px; margin: var(--spacing-medium) 0; overflow-x: auto;">
                <pre style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: monospace; margin: 0; font-size: var(--font-size-small);"><code>Fields:
  id => 'integer'
  file_path => 'varchar(512)' UNIQUE
  file_type => 'enum' (tt, md)
  title => 'varchar(512)'
  excerpt => 'text' (first 500 chars for preview)
  searchable_text => 'longtext' FULLTEXT INDEX (for search)
  content_hash => 'varchar(64)' (SHA256 of .tt file)
  role_access => 'json' (which roles can access)
  indexed_at => 'timestamp'
  last_file_modified => 'timestamp'
  file_size => 'integer'
</code></pre>
            </div>

            <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">4.3 New Table: code_search_index</h3>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Location:</strong> <a href="/Documentation/Result_Class_Development_Guide" target="_blank" style="color: var(--link-color);">/lib/Comserv/Model/Schema/Ency/Result/CodeSearchIndex.pm</a></p>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Purpose:</strong> Index of application source code (.pm and .tt code) for developers/admins</p>
            <div style="background: rgba(255,255,255,0.15); padding: var(--spacing-medium); border-radius: 5px; margin: var(--spacing-medium) 0; overflow-x: auto;">
                <pre style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: monospace; margin: 0; font-size: var(--font-size-small);"><code>Fields:
  id => 'integer'
  file_path => 'varchar(512)' UNIQUE
  file_type => 'enum' (pm, tt, sql)
  code_elements => 'json' ({functions, classes, variables, line_numbers})
  searchable_code => 'longtext' FULLTEXT INDEX
  content_hash => 'varchar(64)'
  indexed_at => 'timestamp'
  min_role => 'varchar' (minimum role to search: developer, admin)
  file_size => 'integer'
</code></pre>
            </div>

            <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">4.4 New Table: web_search_results</h3>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Location:</strong> <a href="/Documentation/Result_Class_Development_Guide" target="_blank" style="color: var(--link-color);">/lib/Comserv/Model/Schema/Ency/Result/WebSearchResult.pm</a></p>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Purpose:</strong> Store web search results BEFORE admin verification. Once verified, can be added to documentation_metadata_index.</p>
            <div style="background: rgba(255,255,255,0.15); padding: var(--spacing-medium); border-radius: 5px; margin: var(--spacing-medium) 0; overflow-x: auto;">
                <pre style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: monospace; margin: 0; font-size: var(--font-size-small);"><code>Fields:
  id => 'integer'
  query => 'varchar(500)' (original search query)
  result_title => 'varchar(512)'
  result_url => 'varchar(1000)'
  result_snippet => 'longtext'
  full_content => 'longtext' (if book/PDF stored)
  source_type => 'enum' (web, public_domain_book, arxiv, etc.)
  found_by_user_id => 'integer'
  is_verified => 'boolean' (admin approval)
  verified_by_user_id => 'integer'
  verification_notes => 'text'
  created_at => 'timestamp'
  verified_at => 'timestamp'
  used_in_ai_message_id => 'integer' (FK to ai_messages)
</code></pre>
            </div>

            <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">4.5 New Table: ai_model_config</h3>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Location:</strong> <a href="/Documentation/Result_Class_Development_Guide" target="_blank" style="color: var(--link-color);">/lib/Comserv/Model/Schema/Ency/Result/AiModelConfig.pm</a></p>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Purpose:</strong> Admin configuration for model access by role</p>
            <div style="background: rgba(255,255,255,0.15); padding: var(--spacing-medium); border-radius: 5px; margin: var(--spacing-medium) 0; overflow-x: auto;">
                <pre style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: monospace; margin: 0; font-size: var(--font-size-small);"><code>Fields:
  id => 'integer'
  role => 'varchar(100)' (admin, developer, user, guest, etc.)
  agent_type => 'varchar(100)' (documentation, helpdesk, ency, etc.)
  model_name => 'varchar(100)' (ollama, xai, etc.)
  enabled => 'boolean'
  api_endpoint => 'varchar(500)' (http://localhost:11434 or https://...)
  api_key_encrypted => 'varchar(512)' (encrypted, Kubernetes-compatible)
  temperature => 'float' (0.0-1.0)
  max_tokens => 'integer'
  search_docs_automatically => 'boolean'
  allow_web_search => 'boolean'
  allow_code_search => 'boolean'
  priority => 'integer' (selection order)
  created_at => 'timestamp'
  updated_at => 'timestamp'
</code></pre>
            </div>

            <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">4.6 New Table: documentation_role_access</h3>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Location:</strong> <a href="/Documentation/Result_Class_Development_Guide" target="_blank" style="color: var(--link-color);">/lib/Comserv/Model/Schema/Ency/Result/DocumentationRoleAccess.pm</a></p>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Purpose:</strong> Fine-grained role-based access to documentation sections</p>
            <div style="background: rgba(255,255,255,0.15); padding: var(--spacing-medium); border-radius: 5px; margin: var(--spacing-medium) 0; overflow-x: auto;">
                <pre style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: monospace; margin: 0; font-size: var(--font-size-small);"><code>Fields:
  id => 'integer'
  role => 'varchar(100)'
  doc_section_pattern => 'varchar(255)' (e.g., 'admin/*', 'tutorial/*', 'api/*')
  can_access => 'boolean' (true=can, false=deny)
  created_at => 'timestamp'
  UNIQUE (role, doc_section_pattern)
</code></pre>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- MULTI-AGENT SYSTEM -->
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-100">
            <h2 id="multi-agent-system" style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">5. Multi-Agent Architecture</h2>

            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">Different AI agents can be configured for different purposes. Each agent has its own:</p>
            <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                <li>Documentation scope (which docs to search)</li>
                <li>System prompt (instructions for AI behavior)</li>
                <li>Models available (Ollama, XAI, etc.)</li>
                <li>User access control (who can use this agent)</li>
                <li>Logging and analytics</li>
            </ul>

            <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">Example Agents:</h3>
            <div style="background: rgba(255,255,255,0.15); padding: var(--spacing-medium); border-radius: 5px; margin: var(--spacing-medium) 0;">
                <table style="width: 100%; color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); border-collapse: collapse;">
                    <thead>
                        <tr style="background: var(--secondary-color, #0066cc); color: white;">
                            <th style="padding: var(--spacing-small); text-align: left; border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">Agent Name</th>
                            <th style="padding: var(--spacing-small); text-align: left; border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">Purpose</th>
                            <th style="padding: var(--spacing-small); text-align: left; border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">Doc Scope</th>
                            <th style="padding: var(--spacing-small); text-align: left; border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">Users</th>
                        </tr>
                    </thead>
                    <tbody>
                        <tr style="background: rgba(255,255,255,0.15);">
                            <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">Documentation Agent</td>
                            <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">General help on using Comserv</td>
                            <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">/Documentation/*</td>
                            <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">All users</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                            <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">Code Assistant</td>
                            <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">Help developers understand code</td>
                            <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">/lib/*, /root/*/</td>
                            <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">Dev/Admin</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr style="background: rgba(255,255,255,0.15);">
                            <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">ENCY Agent</td>
                            <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">Help with inventory/encyclodepdia system</td>
                            <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">ENCY docs + database</td>
                            <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">ENCY users</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                            <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">Beekeeping Agent</td>
                            <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">Beekeeping data & docs</td>
                            <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">Beekeeping docs</td>
                            <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">Beekeeping module users</td>
                        </tr>
                    </tbody>
                </table>
            </div>

            <div style="background: var(--warning-color, #fff3cd); border-left: 4px solid var(--warning-border, #ffc107); padding: var(--spacing-medium); margin: var(--spacing-medium) 0; border-radius: 3px;">
                <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); margin: 0;">
                    <strong>Note:</strong> Multi-agent architecture is designed into the system but Phase 1 focuses on Documentation Agent only. Other agents can be added in future phases by configuring additional rows in ai_model_config table.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- VERIFICATION WORKFLOW -->
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-100">
            <h2 id="verification-workflow" style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">6. Web Search Verification Workflow</h2>

            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">When AI finds information via web search, it should NOT immediately add to knowledge base. Instead:</p>

            <ol style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                <li><strong>Store in web_search_results table:</strong> Mark as is_verified=false</li>
                <li><strong>Notify admin:</strong> New unverified web result needs review</li>
                <li><strong>Admin reviews:</strong> Check accuracy, licensing (for books), relevance</li>
                <li><strong>Admin approves:</strong> Add to documentation_metadata_index OR reject with notes</li>
                <li><strong>Future searches:</strong> Use verified results from documentation_metadata_index (faster, no external API call)</li>
            </ol>

            <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">Admin Dashboard Updates:</h3>
            <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                <li>New section: "Pending Web Search Approvals" with counts and recent submissions</li>
                <li>One-click approve/reject with optional notes</li>
                <li>Ability to edit title/snippet before adding to docs</li>
                <li>Track which user found/verified each result</li>
                <li>Option to import public domain books directly into documentation_metadata_index</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- IMPLEMENTATION PLAN -->
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-100">
            <h2 id="implementation-plan" style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">7. Implementation Plan</h2>

            <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">Key Principles:</h3>
            <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                <li>✅ <strong>Reuse existing code:</strong> Extend AiConversation/AiMessage rather than create new tables</li>
                <li>✅ <strong>Theme-compatible CSS:</strong> Use var(--text-color), var(--header-font), etc. from theme system</li>
                <li>✅ <strong>Template Toolkit integration:</strong> All .tt files use documentation_tt_template.tt as base</li>
                <li>✅ <strong>Use existing database UI:</strong> Leverage Comserv's database management tools instead of raw SQL scripts</li>
                <li>✅ <strong>Docker/Kubernetes ready:</strong> Use EnvFileManager pattern for API key storage (encrypted, container-aware)</li>
                <li>✅ <strong>Never create new file if existing can be extended:</strong> Refactor only if file exceeds reasonable size (~500 lines)</li>
            </ul>

            <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">Phased Approach (8-10 Weeks)</h3>
            <div style="background: rgba(255,255,255,0.15); padding: var(--spacing-medium); border-radius: 5px; margin: var(--spacing-medium) 0; overflow-x: auto;">
                <table style="width: 100%; color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); border-collapse: collapse;">
                    <thead>
                        <tr style="background: var(--secondary-color, #0066cc); color: white;">
                            <th style="padding: var(--spacing-small); text-align: left; border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">Phase</th>
                            <th style="padding: var(--spacing-small); text-align: left; border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">Duration</th>
                            <th style="padding: var(--spacing-small); text-align: left; border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">Deliverables</th>
                        </tr>
                    </thead>
                    <tbody>
                        <tr style="background: #d4edda;">
                            <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);"><strong>✅ 1: Database & Model Layer</strong></td>
                            <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);"><strong>COMPLETED Dec 25</strong></td>
                            <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">
                                ✅ AiMessage.pm (with new fields)<br>
                                ✅ DocumentationMetadataIndex.pm (created + fixed)<br>
                                ✅ CodeSearchIndex.pm (created)<br>
                                ✅ WebSearchResult.pm (created)<br>
                                ✅ AiModelConfig.pm (created)<br>
                                ✅ DocumentationRoleAccess.pm (created)<br>
                                ✅ <strong>All tables created in ENCY database and automated startup initialization</strong>
                            </td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                            <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">2: Backend Services</td>
                            <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">2-3 weeks</td>
                            <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">
                                • DocumentationIndexer service<br>
                                • LLMOllama service<br>
                                • LLMXAI service (with encryption)<br>
                                • 🆕 LLMGrok service (Grok API integration with encrypted API key)<br>
                                • Extend Chat::AI controller<br>
                                • Role-based access filtering<br>
                                • 🆕 Model configuration endpoints (allow dynamic model switching)
                            </td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr style="background: rgba(255,255,255,0.15);">
                            <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">3: Frontend & UI</td>
                            <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">2-3 weeks</td>
                            <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">
                                • Chat widget HTML/CSS (theme-compatible)<br>
                                • 🆕 Chat widget CSS redesign matching Grok.ai aesthetic (dark theme, modern typography)<br>
                                • JavaScript chat logic<br>
                                • Model selector dropdown (Ollama, XAI, Grok options)<br>
                                • Message history UI<br>
