    <!-- SECURITY & KUBERNETES -->
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-100">
            <h2 id="security" style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">8. Security & Kubernetes Compatibility</h2>

            <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">8.1 API Key Management (Docker/Kubernetes)</h3>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Pattern:</strong> Use EnvFileManager or existing .env approach:</p>
            <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                <li>Store encrypted API keys in ai_model_config.api_key_encrypted</li>
                <li>Load encryption key from environment variable: $COMSERV_ENCRYPTION_KEY</li>
                <li>In Kubernetes: set via Secret and mounted as env var</li>
                <li>In Docker: set via docker-compose environment section</li>
                <li>Never log or expose keys in responses</li>
            </ul>

            <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">8.2 Role-Based Access Enforcement</h3>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>CRITICAL:</strong> Always check documentation_role_access table:</p>
            <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                <li>Search returns only docs user can access</li>
                <li>Code search restricted to dev/admin roles</li>
                <li>Web search configurable per role</li>
                <li>Audit log includes user role at time of query</li>
            </ul>

            <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">8.3 Prompt Injection & Output Safety</h3>
            <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                <li>Sanitize user input before LLM (escape quotes, truncate length)</li>
                <li>Sanitize LLM output before display (prevent XSS in HTML)</li>
                <li>Use parameterized database queries</li>
                <li>Rate limiting: 10 messages per user per hour</li>
            </ul>

            <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">8.4 Audit Trail</h3>
            <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                <li>All ai_messages include: user_id, user_role, timestamp, IP address</li>
                <li>Model used, tokens consumed, response time tracked</li>
                <li>Sources cited recorded for verification</li>
                <li>Admin can query by user, date, model, role for investigation</li>
            </ul>

            <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">8.5 Network Configuration (Production)</h3>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Ollama Server Setup:</strong></p>
            <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                <li>Production container (app) needs access to Ollama at 192.168.1.199:11434</li>
                <li>Docker network configuration: allow traffic between containers</li>
                <li>docker-compose.prod.yml: add 192.168.1.199 to hosts or network bridge</li>
                <li>Test endpoint connectivity before deployment</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- SUCCESS CRITERIA -->
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-100">
            <h2 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">9. Success Criteria</h2>

            <div style="background: var(--success-color, #d4edda); border-left: 4px solid var(--success-border, #28a745); padding: var(--spacing-medium); margin: var(--spacing-medium) 0; border-radius: 3px;">
                <strong style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">Feature complete when:</strong>
                <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); margin: var(--spacing-small) 0;">
                    <li>✅ Chat widget visible on all pages (non-auth and authenticated users)</li>
                    <li>✅ Users can ask questions and receive answers in &lt;3s (Ollama)</li>
                    <li>✅ All Q&A logged with metadata in ai_messages table</li>
                    <li>✅ Role-based access enforced (users only see permitted docs)</li>
                    <li>✅ Admins can view conversation logs + analytics</li>
                    <li>✅ Web search results stored and verification workflow functional</li>
                    <li>✅ Code search working for developers/admins</li>
                    <li>✅ API keys encrypted and Kubernetes-compatible</li>
                    <li>✅ All templates conform to <a href="/Documentation/documentation_tt_template" target="_blank" style="color: var(--link-color);">documentation_tt_template.tt</a></li>
                    <li>✅ CSS theme-compatible (var(--*) variables used)</li>
                    <li>✅ Tests passing (unit, integration, role-based access)</li>
                    <li>✅ Documentation/tutorial for users on how to use AI chat</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

